---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The 39-Day Distraction: How Workplaces Are Handling The Tournament" description="With games airing during working hours across multiple time zones, here is how top companies are navigating it.">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-4 bg-[#F7803C]">
    <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl bg-white border-[4px] border-black p-8 md:p-12 shadow-[12px_12px_0px_#2E0D23] relative z-20">
      <div class="inline-block bg-yellow-300 text-black border-[3px] border-black font-black px-4 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">WORK & LIFE</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-6 leading-none" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">
        The 39-Day Distraction: How Workplaces Are Handling The Tournament
      </h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-black font-medium leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-black border-l-8 border-l-blue-600">
          Listen, HR departments across the Americas are literally panicking right now. With 104 matches spread across 39 days, and kickoff times landing right in the middle of the 9-to-5, corporate productivity is about to absolutely tank.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">1. The "WFH" Loophole</h2>
        <p>
          Let's be real, "Work From Home" during June and July of 2026 is going to mean "Watch Football at Home." We are already seeing tech companies leaning into it rather than fighting it. If you have a chill boss, expect "watch parties" to be disguised as "all-hands syncs." If your boss is a micromanager, it's time to invest in a second monitor and master the alt-tab quickswap.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">2. Time Zone Chaos</h2>
        <p>
          Because matches are split between PST, CST, and EST, there is literally no safe time. You might have a 12:00 PM EST match in New York, followed immediately by a 3:00 PM EST match in Texas, capping off with a 6:00 PM EST match in Los Angeles. That is 6 straight hours of football during the workday.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">3. How to Finesse Your Calendar</h2>
        <p>
          Pro-tip: Block out your calendar *now* as "Focus Time" for the specific group stage matches you care about. When the Round of 32 hits, the stakes are too high. Do not let Chad from accounting schedule a Q3 alignment sync during a penalty shootout. Just don't let it happen.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-between items-center border-t-[4px] border-black pt-6">
        <a href="/blog" class="font-outfit text-xl uppercase text-black hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors">← Back to Guides</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
